quote: How to replace the windshield washer pump? (Scenario 1)
author: Disconnect the battery, locate the pump near the washer fluid reservoir, unplug the electrical connector, remove the old pump, and install a new one. Reconnect the wiring and test the pump.

quote: What should I do if my car is pulling to one side? (Scenario 1)
author: Check the tire pressure, ensure even tire wear, inspect the wheel alignment, and adjust if necessary. If the problem persists, check the brakes and suspension components.

quote: How to install a new fuel filter? (Scenario 1)
author: Depressurize the fuel system, disconnect the fuel lines, remove the old filter, and replace it with a new one. Reconnect the fuel lines and check for leaks.

quote: What are the steps to change the engine oil? (Scenario 1)
author: Warm up the engine, place the car on a level surface, remove the oil drain plug, drain the old oil, replace the oil filter, and refill with the recommended oil type.

quote: How to troubleshoot a faulty alternator? (Scenario 1)
author: Check the battery voltage, inspect the alternator belt for wear, test the alternator output with a multimeter, and replace if the voltage is below the recommended range.

quote: Procedure for replacing the car's exhaust manifold gasket. (Scenario 1)
author: Disconnect the battery, remove the exhaust manifold bolts, detach the old gasket, clean the surfaces, and install a new gasket. Reassemble and tighten the bolts to the correct torque specification.

quote: How to fix a leaking sunroof? (Scenario 1)
author: Inspect the sunroof seals for damage or debris, clean the tracks and drains, and replace any worn seals. Test for leaks by pouring water over the sunroof.

quote: Instructions to replace a car's brake master cylinder. (Scenario 1)
author: Remove the brake fluid from the reservoir, disconnect the brake lines, unbolt the old master cylinder, install the new one, and bleed the brakes to remove air from the system.

quote: How to check and replace the spark plug wires? (Scenario 1)
author: Remove the old spark plug wires one at a time to avoid mixing them up, inspect for wear or damage, and replace with new wires of the same length and type.

quote: What to do if the car's air conditioning is not cooling? (Scenario 1)
author: Check the refrigerant level, inspect the compressor and condenser for damage, check for leaks, and recharge the system with the correct refrigerant type if needed.

quote: How to clean a mass airflow sensor? (Scenario 1)
author: Disconnect the battery, remove the sensor, spray the sensor with a specialized cleaner, allow it to dry completely, and reinstall the sensor. Do not touch the sensor element.

quote: Procedure for replacing a damaged radiator. (Scenario 1)
author: Drain the coolant, disconnect the radiator hoses, remove the radiator mounting bolts, install the new radiator, reconnect the hoses, refill with coolant, and check for leaks.

quote: How to adjust the car's seat belts? (Scenario 1)
author: Locate the seat belt adjustment points, loosen the bolts, adjust the belt to the desired position, and tighten the bolts securely.

quote: Steps to replace a worn-out cabin air filter. (Scenario 1)
author: Open the glove compartment, remove the retaining clips, take out the old cabin air filter, and replace it with a new one. Reinstall the clips and close the glove compartment.

quote: How to diagnose a faulty oxygen sensor? (Scenario 1)
author: Check for diagnostic trouble codes (DTCs) using an OBD-II scanner, inspect the sensor and wiring for damage, and replace the sensor if faulty.

quote: Instructions to replace the timing chain tensioner. (Scenario 1)
author: Remove the timing cover, loosen the tensioner bolts, remove the old tensioner, install a new one, and adjust to the correct tension. Reassemble the engine components.

quote: How to repair a damaged front bumper? (Scenario 1)
author: Remove the bumper cover, repair cracks or holes with filler, sand and smooth the surface, repaint if necessary, and reinstall the bumper cover.

quote: What to do if the power steering pump is noisy? (Scenario 1)
author: Check the power steering fluid level, inspect the pump for leaks, replace the fluid if contaminated, and check the drive belt for proper tension.

quote: Procedure for replacing a faulty fuel injector. (Scenario 1)
author: Depressurize the fuel system, disconnect the electrical connectors, remove the fuel rail, replace the faulty injector, and reassemble in reverse order.

quote: How to troubleshoot a car that stalls unexpectedly? (Scenario 1)
author: Check for fuel delivery issues, inspect the air intake system, test the ignition components, and check for any stored error codes using a diagnostic scanner.

quote: How to install a new fuel filter? (Scenario 15)
author: Depressurize the fuel system, disconnect the fuel lines, remove the old filter, and replace it with a new one. Reconnect the fuel lines and check for leaks.

quote: What are the steps to change the engine oil? (Scenario 15)
author: Warm up the engine, place the car on a level surface, remove the oil drain plug, drain the old oil, replace the oil filter, and refill with the recommended oil type.

quote: How to troubleshoot a faulty alternator? (Scenario 15)
author: Check the battery voltage, inspect the alternator belt for wear, test the alternator output with a multimeter, and replace if the voltage is below the recommended range.

quote: Procedure for replacing the car's exhaust manifold gasket. (Scenario 15)
author: Disconnect the battery, remove the exhaust manifold bolts, detach the old gasket, clean the surfaces, and install a new gasket. Reassemble and tighten the bolts to the correct torque specification.

quote: How to fix a leaking sunroof? (Scenario 15)
author: Inspect the sunroof seals for damage or debris, clean the tracks and drains, and replace any worn seals. Test for leaks by pouring water over the sunroof.

quote: Instructions to replace a car's brake master cylinder. (Scenario 15)
author: Remove the brake fluid from the reservoir, disconnect the brake lines, unbolt the old master cylinder, install the new one, and bleed the brakes to remove air from the system.

quote: How to check and replace the spark plug wires? (Scenario 15)
author: Remove the old spark plug wires one at a time to avoid mixing them up, inspect for wear or damage, and replace with new wires of the same length and type.

quote: What to do if the car's air conditioning is not cooling? (Scenario 15)

quote: Procedure for replacing the car's exhaust manifold gasket. (Scenario 50)
author: Disconnect the battery, remove the exhaust manifold bolts, detach the old gasket, clean the surfaces, and install a new gasket. Reassemble and tighten the bolts to the correct torque specification.

quote: How to fix a leaking sunroof? (Scenario 50)
author: Inspect the sunroof seals for damage or debris, clean the tracks and drains, and replace any worn seals. Test for leaks by pouring water over the sunroof.

quote: Instructions to replace a car's brake master cylinder. (Scenario 50)
author: Remove the brake fluid from the reservoir, disconnect the brake lines, unbolt the old master cylinder, install the new one, and bleed the brakes to remove air from the system.

quote: How to check and replace the spark plug wires? (Scenario 50)
author: Remove the old spark plug wires one at a time to avoid mixing them up, inspect for wear or damage, and replace with new wires of the same length and type.

quote: What to do if the car's air conditioning is not cooling? (Scenario 50)
author: Check the refrigerant level, inspect the compressor and condenser for damage, check for leaks, and recharge the system with the correct refrigerant type if needed.

quote: How to clean a mass airflow sensor? (Scenario 50)
author: Disconnect the battery, remove the sensor, spray the sensor with a specialized cleaner, allow it to dry completely, and reinstall the sensor. Do not touch the sensor element.

quote: Procedure for replacing a damaged radiator. (Scenario 50)
author: Drain the coolant, disconnect the radiator hoses, remove the radiator mounting bolts, install the new radiator, reconnect the hoses, refill with coolant, and check for leaks.

quote: How to adjust the car's seat belts? (Scenario 50)
author: Locate the seat belt adjustment points, loosen the bolts, adjust the belt to the desired position, and tighten the bolts securely.

quote: Steps to replace a worn-out cabin air filter. (Scenario 50)
author: Open the glove compartment, remove the retaining clips, take out the old cabin air filter, and replace it with a new one. Reinstall the clips and close the glove compartment.

quote: How to diagnose a faulty oxygen sensor? (Scenario 50)
author: Check for diagnostic trouble codes (DTCs) using an OBD-II scanner, inspect the sensor and wiring for damage, and replace the sensor if faulty.

quote: Instructions to replace the timing chain tensioner. (Scenario 50)
author: Remove the timing cover, loosen the tensioner bolts, remove the old tensioner, install a new one, and adjust to the correct tension. Reassemble the engine components.

quote: How to repair a damaged front bumper? (Scenario 50)
author: Remove the bumper cover, repair cracks or holes with filler, sand and smooth the surface, repaint if necessary, and reinstall the bumper cover.

quote: What to do if the power steering pump is noisy? (Scenario 50)
author: Check the power steering fluid level, inspect the pump for leaks, replace the fluid if contaminated, and check the drive belt for proper tension.

quote: Procedure for replacing a faulty fuel injector. (Scenario 50)
author: Depressurize the fuel system, disconnect the electrical connectors, remove the fuel rail, replace the faulty injector, and reassemble in reverse order.

quote: How to troubleshoot a car that stalls unexpectedly? (Scenario 50)
author: Check for fuel delivery issues, inspect the air intake system, test the ignition components, and check for any stored error codes using a diagnostic scanner.

quote: How to change car engine
author: First things first, remove the bonnet and disconnect your battery.Drain all the fluids from your engine.Disconnect the intake, coolant lines and radiator, and the exhaust.Disconnect accessories and hoses.Double check everything.
